					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13148552#post-4558083</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13148552/scp-5058#post-4558083</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2020 10:19:32 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>3146689</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>The bit of &quot;let the waves go&quot; immediately made me imagine some surfer dude wisdom</p> </blockquote> <p>There are other types of waves except the sea ones. Radio waves, for example. The context for the whole thing goes something like this:</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The message itself, combined with what happened to the Foundation personnel, might mean that if the aliens were doing all of this on purpose, they realized what the Foundation was trying to do. Then they decided to warn us, by using the message and demonstrating what they're capable of in the process (hence weird memetic images that cause people <em>with resistance</em> to lose their minds). Basically they want us to stay out of this, and if we won't, they probably have something to make us do so.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13148552#post-4557374</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13148552/scp-5058#post-4557374</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2020 22:01:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>augmentedspartan</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1775542</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm gonna admit that the final image went over my head. I was pretty hooked before that, but the ending simply confused me. The bit of &quot;let the waves go&quot; immediately made me imagine some surfer dude wisdom, which doesn't really mesh well with an unsettling tone.</p> <p>What I'm getting is that the aliens are admitting to studying humans, but that's pretty much a given from the radio waves emissions and alien fiction in general. Not sure what else I'm supposed to get from the image, though.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13148552#post-4547659</guid>
				<title>Human post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13148552/scp-5058#post-4547659</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2020 17:58:51 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>3146689</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So, with the 3rd jamcon theme, I realized we could delve a bit more into strange/unsettling territory, so here's my take.</p> <p>This SCP is my love letter to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=Local+58">Local 58</a> and similar obscure, unsettling alien-based horror out there. They just keep proving that it doesn't matter how overdone a certain idea is, you can still do it in a cool and original way if you try hard enough.</p> <p><strong>Fellow human persons who gave their human feedback on this:</strong> <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5336470&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1584211296" alt="cybersqyd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5336470)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cybersqyd" >cybersqyd</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tanhony" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=776854&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1584211296" alt="Tanhony" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=776854)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tanhony" >Tanhony</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/henzoid" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5190300&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1584211296" alt="Henzoid" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5190300)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/henzoid" >Henzoid</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/deadly-bread" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3988532&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1584211296" alt="Deadly Bread" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3988532)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/deadly-bread" >Deadly Bread</a></span>, and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drakimoto" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5255688&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1584211296" alt="DrAkimoto" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5255688)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drakimoto" >DrAkimoto</a></span>.</p> <p>Image attribution goes something like this: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:House_party_in_Denver_Colorado.JPG#filelinks">one</a>, <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Waxing_crescent_moon.jpg">two</a>. The images were edited by me.</p> 
